{
  "stem": "7598.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He sold and bought bread.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He belonged to a Zionist organization and altogether [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] was more enterprising than perhaps my uncle who was a father of children.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He-- this cousin came up to my uncle and said, I could organize a passeur, which translated is, is the word smuggler.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it isn't really a smuggler.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It is just people who know, who knew how to cross the frontiers between Belgium and France.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that for 20,000 Belgian francs, they could organize our escape to unoccupied France. 20,000 Belgian francs is, in those days, is equivalent of 25,000 pounds.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, it was per family.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Strange thing-- my cousin tells me that there were people-- for us, it was a lot of money.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't know what my family possessed, but it wasn't sort of all that much.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Anyway, according to my cousin, my father took-- my uncle took the plunge only because of my brother and myself.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I hoped that we would be able to be reunited.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And fortunately, as I said, he had the funds and not my father.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And therefore, we were able to organize the escape.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] On the 15th of October, 1941, which is also my, my brother's birthday, we left.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I-- my brother was told about it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We girls weren't, but I had an inkling.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "First of all, it was the only thing that I thought of all the time was to try and get away and be reunited with my parents.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I think a girl of 13 needs her parents perhaps more than a son.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Also something which I understand now but didn't understand then-- there were three girls and one boy in that family.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
